        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I think beguile just has a bigger chance to not last as long as thrall.  I use thrall alot and seems to last eighther very short time or very long time never medium time.  Now the cool think about charming hard hitting undead mobs is you can park them way away from you.  This gives you plenty of time to fd or mez if and when it breaks.  I also dont think charisma has anything (or at least not much) to do with charm for necros.  Id rather max out hp so if u do get hit by 2 MOBS then at least u have a little buffer of hp to fd with instead of gimping yourself with a bunch of crap stat charisma items.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
